WEBVTT

00:01.034 --> 00:02.969
GILES: Previously.
I love you.

00:03.003 --> 00:06.073
-Oh, my God.
-Here lies the warrior
of the people.

00:06.107 --> 00:08.976
Let her cross over.

00:09.009 --> 00:13.846
But I think I was in heaven.
I was torn out of there...
by my friends.

00:13.881 --> 00:16.082
-They can never know.
-GILES: We can't ignore
this kind of behavior.

00:16.117 --> 00:18.885
Something needs to be done
 before it spins out of control.

00:18.919 --> 00:21.021
BUFFY:
I'm glad you're here
to take care of it.

00:21.054 --> 00:23.157
-We're getting married.
-TARA: Congratulations.

00:23.190 --> 00:25.092
Willow, you are using
 too much magic.

00:25.126 --> 00:28.329
-Can we not do this now?
-Just forget it ever happened.

00:28.361 --> 00:29.763
Forget.

00:57.490 --> 01:00.561
(show-tune music playing)

01:07.234 --> 01:09.736
(alarm ringing)

01:40.533 --> 01:43.471
(ringing)

02:15.468 --> 02:18.138
* Every single night
the same arrangement *

02:18.171 --> 02:20.873
* I go out
and fight the fight *

02:20.908 --> 02:23.443
* Still I always feel
the strange estrangement *

02:23.477 --> 02:26.180
* Nothing here is real
Nothing here is right *

02:26.213 --> 02:29.616
* I've been making shows
of trading blows *

02:29.650 --> 02:33.853
* Just hoping no one knows
that I've been going
through the motions *

02:33.887 --> 02:36.389
* Walking through the part

02:36.424 --> 02:38.991
* Nothing seems
to penetrate *

02:39.026 --> 02:41.895
* My heart

02:41.929 --> 02:44.731
* I was always brave
and kind of righteous *

02:44.764 --> 02:47.735
* Now I find
I'm wavering *

02:47.768 --> 02:50.903
* Crawl out of your grave
you find this fight
just doesn't mean a thing *

02:50.937 --> 02:53.373
* She ain't got
that swing *

02:53.406 --> 02:55.975
* Thanks for noticing

02:56.009 --> 02:58.478
* She does pretty well
with fiends from hell *

02:58.512 --> 03:00.348
* But lately
we can tell *

03:00.381 --> 03:02.915
* That she's just
going through the motions *

03:02.949 --> 03:06.419
* Going through the motions
* Faking it somehow

03:06.454 --> 03:09.356
* She's not even
half the girl she--*

03:09.389 --> 03:12.058
* Ow

03:12.092 --> 03:14.495
* Will I stay
this way forever *

03:14.527 --> 03:17.431
* Sleepwalk through
my life's endeavor *

03:17.465 --> 03:19.832
* How can I repay--
* Whatever

03:19.866 --> 03:23.871
* I don't want to be

03:23.903 --> 03:26.606
* Going through
the motions *

03:26.639 --> 03:29.209
* Losing all my drive

03:29.242 --> 03:31.711
* I can't even see

03:31.745 --> 03:34.548
* If this is really me

03:34.581 --> 03:37.617
* And I just wanna be

03:37.651 --> 03:43.557
* Alive

03:51.932 --> 03:53.933
GILES:
Good morning, Buffy.

03:53.966 --> 03:56.870
Oh, hey. Did Dawn get off
to school all right?

03:56.903 --> 03:59.740
What? Oh, uh, yeah,
I think so.

04:01.241 --> 04:03.776
Respect the cruller
and tame the doughnut!

04:03.811 --> 04:05.812
That's still funny, sweetie.

04:05.846 --> 04:08.915
So, uh, no research?

04:08.949 --> 04:11.685
Nothing going on,
monsters or whatnot?

04:13.020 --> 04:15.688
Good. Good.

04:15.788 --> 04:18.992
Uh, so did anybody, uh,

04:19.026 --> 04:22.762
last night, you know,
did anybody, um,

04:22.795 --> 04:24.632
burst into song?

04:26.867 --> 04:28.401
Merciful Zeus!

04:28.435 --> 04:30.338
We thought
it was just us.

04:30.370 --> 04:32.439
Well, I sang, but I had
my guitar there, so--
 It was bizarre.

04:32.473 --> 04:34.908
We were talking.
Then it was like--
Like you were in a musical.

04:34.942 --> 04:37.577
That would explain
the huge backing orchestra
I couldn't see

04:37.610 --> 04:40.012
and the synchronized dancing
from the room service chaps.
 We were arguing.

04:40.047 --> 04:42.149
Then everything rhymed,
and there were harmonies

04:42.182 --> 04:44.317
and a dance with coconuts.
It was very disturbing.

04:44.351 --> 04:45.886
What did you sing about?

04:47.355 --> 04:48.822
I don't remember.

04:48.855 --> 04:51.124
But it seemed
perfectly normal.

04:51.158 --> 04:54.427
But disturbing and not
the natural order of things, and
do you think it'll happen again?

04:54.461 --> 04:57.129
-I don't know.
We should look into it.
-WILLOW: With the books.

04:57.230 --> 04:58.865
Do we have any
books on this?

04:58.899 --> 05:00.533
Well, we just gotta
break it down,

05:00.567 --> 05:02.302
look at the factors
before it happens again,

05:02.336 --> 05:05.271
'cause I, for one--
* I've got a theory
that it's a demon *

05:05.305 --> 05:07.940
* A dancing demon
No, something
isn't right there *

05:07.975 --> 05:10.478
* I've got a theory
Some kid is dreaming *

05:10.511 --> 05:13.279
* And we're all stuck inside
his wacky Broadway nightmare *

05:13.312 --> 05:17.617
* I've got a theory
We should work this out *

05:17.651 --> 05:19.720
* It's getting eerie

05:19.752 --> 05:25.292
* What's this cheery
singing all about *

05:25.324 --> 05:27.394
* It could be witches
some evil witches *

05:27.427 --> 05:30.029
* Which is ridiculous
'cause witches
they were persecuted *

05:30.062 --> 05:33.733
* Wicca good and love the Earth
and women power
and I'll be over here *

05:33.766 --> 05:36.536
* I've got a theory
It could be bunnies *

05:36.569 --> 05:38.672
(crickets chirping)

05:38.706 --> 05:41.509
-* I've got a--
-* Bunnies aren't just cute

05:41.542 --> 05:44.377
* Like everybody supposes

05:44.411 --> 05:46.814
* They got them hoppy legs

05:46.846 --> 05:49.348
* And twitchy little noses

05:49.382 --> 05:51.218
* And what's with
all the carrots *

05:51.250 --> 05:56.990
* What do they need such
good eyesight for anyway *

05:57.024 --> 06:02.194
* Bunnies, bunnies
It must be bunnies *

06:04.865 --> 06:06.567
* Or maybe midgets

06:06.600 --> 06:11.504
* I've got a theory
We should work this fast *

06:11.538 --> 06:14.408
BOTH:
* Because it clearly
could get serious *

06:14.442 --> 06:17.778
* Before it's passed

06:17.810 --> 06:19.747
BUFFY:
* I've got a theory

06:19.779 --> 06:23.716
* It doesn't matter

06:23.750 --> 06:28.721
* What can't we face
if we're together *

06:28.755 --> 06:32.893
* What's in this place
that we can't weather *

06:32.925 --> 06:34.927
* Apocalypse

06:34.961 --> 06:38.264
* We've all been there

06:38.298 --> 06:40.300
* The same old trips

06:40.332 --> 06:44.237
* Why should we care

06:44.271 --> 06:49.042
ALL:
* What can't we do
if we get in it *

06:49.076 --> 06:53.045
* We'll work it through
within a minute *

06:53.079 --> 06:55.649
* We have to try

06:55.682 --> 06:58.250
* We'll pay the price

06:58.284 --> 07:00.954
* It's do or die

07:00.987 --> 07:04.492
* Hey, I've died twice

07:04.524 --> 07:06.593
ALL:
* What can't we face

07:06.627 --> 07:09.663
* What can't we face
* If we're together

07:09.697 --> 07:12.231
* What's in this place
that we can't weather *

07:12.264 --> 07:14.334
GILES:
* If we're together

07:14.367 --> 07:17.637
* There's nothing
we can't face *

07:17.670 --> 07:20.273
* Except for bunnies

07:23.610 --> 07:27.247
See? Okay,
that was disturbing.
I thought it was neat.

07:27.279 --> 07:29.649
So what is it?
What's causing it?

07:30.817 --> 07:32.586
I thought it didn't matter.

07:32.620 --> 07:36.456
Well, I'm not
exactly quaking in my
stylish-yet-affordable boots,

07:36.490 --> 07:39.158
but there's definitely
something unnatural
going on here.

07:39.192 --> 07:41.894
And that
doesn't usually lead
to hugs and puppies.

07:43.831 --> 07:45.298
Well, is it just us?

07:45.331 --> 07:47.300
Is it only
happening to us?

07:47.334 --> 07:49.468
Because
that would probably
mean a spell.

07:52.973 --> 07:57.677
* They got
the mustard out *

07:57.711 --> 08:03.250
* They got
the mustard out *

08:08.689 --> 08:10.490
It's not just us.

08:12.860 --> 08:16.463
Oh, my God. You will never
believe what happened
at school today.

08:16.495 --> 08:18.865
Everybody started
singing and dancing?

08:20.500 --> 08:22.401
I gave birth
to a pterodactyl.

08:22.435 --> 08:25.338
Oh, my God.
Did it sing?

08:25.372 --> 08:28.507
-(whispering)
-So, you guys too, huh?

08:28.542 --> 08:31.110
-So what'd you sing about?
-Math.

08:32.211 --> 08:35.548
That's right.
The volume. The text.

08:36.616 --> 08:37.850
What text?

08:38.951 --> 08:40.653
The volumey text.

08:40.687 --> 08:41.922
You know.

08:43.289 --> 08:45.692
The (mumbles)
report.

08:45.725 --> 08:48.895
-The what now?
-There's just a few volumes

08:48.928 --> 08:51.831
back at the house
that deal with
mystical chants, bacchanals.

08:51.865 --> 08:54.701
-Might be relevant.
-Yeah, we could, um--

08:54.735 --> 08:58.572
I'm a hairsbreadth from
investigating bunnies at the
moment, so I'm open to anything.

08:58.605 --> 09:01.908
Great. We'll, um,
check it out, and, um,
we'll give you a call.

09:01.942 --> 09:05.177
Yeah. This could blow
the whole thing wide open.

09:05.211 --> 09:07.547
Do we have any books
at all at home?

09:07.648 --> 09:10.750
Well, who wants to be
cooped up on a day like this?

09:10.783 --> 09:14.754
The sun is shining.
There are songs going on.

09:14.788 --> 09:16.756
Those guys
are checking you out.

09:16.789 --> 09:19.359
What? Wh-What are they
looking at?

09:19.392 --> 09:21.394
The hotness
of you, doofus.

09:21.427 --> 09:23.296
Those boys really
thought I was hot?

09:23.330 --> 09:25.365
Entirely.

09:25.398 --> 09:27.967
Oh, my God.
I'm cured.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.437
I want the boys!
(chuckles)

09:30.470 --> 09:32.471
Do I have to fight
to keep you?

09:32.504 --> 09:34.441
'Cause I'm not
large with the butch.

09:34.474 --> 09:37.076
I'm just not
used to that.

09:37.110 --> 09:39.712
They were really
looking at me?

09:39.746 --> 09:42.215
And you can't imagine
what they see in you.

09:42.249 --> 09:45.251
I know exactly
what they see in me.

09:45.284 --> 09:47.386
You.

09:47.419 --> 09:51.290
* I lived my life
in shadow *

09:51.323 --> 09:56.062
* Never the sun
on my face *

09:56.096 --> 09:59.767
* It didn't seem
so sad though *

09:59.799 --> 10:03.770
* I figured
that was my place *

10:03.803 --> 10:08.140
* Now I'm bathed in light

10:08.174 --> 10:12.345
* Something
just isn't right *

10:12.379 --> 10:15.182
* I'm under your spell

10:15.215 --> 10:17.616
* How else could it be

10:17.650 --> 10:20.253
* Anyone would notice me

10:20.287 --> 10:23.456
* It's magic, I can tell

10:23.490 --> 10:25.491
* How you set me free

10:25.524 --> 10:28.928
* Brought me out
so easily *

10:28.961 --> 10:32.765
* I saw a world
enchanted *

10:32.799 --> 10:37.303
* Spirits and charms
in the air *

10:37.336 --> 10:41.274
* I always
took for granted *

10:41.307 --> 10:45.177
* I was the only one
there *

10:45.211 --> 10:49.515
* But your
power shone *

10:49.548 --> 10:53.821
* Brighter than
any I've known *

10:53.854 --> 10:56.956
* I'm under your spell

10:56.990 --> 10:59.192
* Nothing I can do

10:59.225 --> 11:01.794
* You just took
my soul with you *

11:01.828 --> 11:04.230
* You worked
your charm so well *

11:04.264 --> 11:06.298
* Finally I knew

11:06.332 --> 11:09.302
* Everything
I dreamed was true *

11:09.336 --> 11:15.075
* You make me believe

11:26.552 --> 11:30.490
* The moon to the tide

11:30.523 --> 11:34.927
* I can feel you inside

11:34.961 --> 11:37.831
* I'm under your spell

11:37.865 --> 11:40.200
* Surging like the sea

11:40.232 --> 11:42.870
* Pulled to you
so helplessly *

11:42.903 --> 11:46.173
* I break
with every swell *

11:46.206 --> 11:48.240
* Lost in ecstasy

11:48.274 --> 11:50.710
* Spread beneath
my willow tree *

11:50.744 --> 11:52.946
* You make me

11:52.980 --> 11:58.284
* Complete

12:02.322 --> 12:06.393
* You make me complete

12:06.426 --> 12:10.297
* You make me complete

12:10.330 --> 12:12.032
* You make me--*

12:12.065 --> 12:14.533
I bet they're
not even working.
Who now?

12:14.567 --> 12:18.038
Willow and Tara.
You see the way they were
with each other?

12:18.071 --> 12:20.774
The get-a-roominess
of them? I bet they're--

12:22.274 --> 12:25.577
Singing.
They're probably
singing right now.

12:25.611 --> 12:27.815
I'm sure Willow and Tara
are making every effort.

12:27.847 --> 12:30.283
Oh, yeah.
Xander.

12:30.317 --> 12:32.751
Buffy, it's okay.
I do know
about this stuff.

12:32.786 --> 12:36.322
Besides, it's all
kind of romantic.

12:36.355 --> 12:38.125
BOTH:
No, it's not.

12:38.158 --> 12:40.994
Come on.
Songs, dancing around.

12:41.028 --> 12:42.995
What's gonna be
wrong with that?

12:43.029 --> 12:45.365
(tap dancing)

12:47.801 --> 12:51.938
(whimpering)

13:01.981 --> 13:03.884
(screams)

13:09.489 --> 13:11.825
That's entertainment.

13:18.697 --> 13:20.267
XANDER:
You want some
breakfast, baby?

13:20.299 --> 13:22.970
You don't have
to go to work?

13:23.003 --> 13:25.172
No. I shut the crew
down for the day.

13:25.205 --> 13:27.274
My guys started
dancing around me.

13:27.307 --> 13:29.442
I don't know
if I could deal.

13:29.475 --> 13:34.447
It's a flab thing.
So, waffles?

13:34.480 --> 13:37.283
Will you still
make me waffles
when we're married?

13:37.317 --> 13:39.318
No, I'll only
make them for myself,

13:39.351 --> 13:42.154
but by California law,
you will own half of them.

13:44.224 --> 13:47.460
Hey, how about omelets?
I could do an omelet...

13:47.494 --> 13:50.797
* This is the man
that I plan to entangle *

13:50.830 --> 13:54.400
* Isn't he fine

13:54.433 --> 13:57.870
* My claim to fame
was to maim and to mangle *

13:57.904 --> 14:01.240
* Vengeance was mine

14:01.274 --> 14:04.644
* But I'm out of the biz

14:04.677 --> 14:08.315
* The name I made
I'll trade for his *

14:08.347 --> 14:11.985
* The only trouble is

14:12.019 --> 14:14.453
* I'll never tell

14:16.556 --> 14:19.558
* She is the one
She's such wonderful fun *

14:19.591 --> 14:21.693
* Such passion
and grace *

14:23.562 --> 14:26.198
* Warm in the night
when I'm right
in her tight *

14:26.232 --> 14:29.668
* Embrace
tight embrace *

14:29.701 --> 14:33.273
* I'll never
let her go *

14:33.306 --> 14:36.408
* The love we've known
can only grow *

14:36.442 --> 14:38.278
* There's just
one thing that-- *

14:38.311 --> 14:40.379
No.

14:40.413 --> 14:41.981
* I'll never tell

14:43.283 --> 14:47.955
BOTH:
* 'Cause there's
nothing to tell *

14:51.224 --> 14:53.360
* He snores
* She wheezes

14:53.393 --> 14:55.195
* Say "housework"
and he freezes *

14:55.227 --> 14:58.431
* She eats
these skeezy cheeses
that I can't describe *

14:58.465 --> 15:01.969
* I talk, he breezes
* She doesn't know
what pleases *

15:02.001 --> 15:05.138
* His penis got diseases
from a Chumash tribe *

15:05.172 --> 15:07.874
* The vibe

15:07.907 --> 15:12.245
* Gets kind of scary

15:12.278 --> 15:14.047
* Like she thinks
I'm ordinary *

15:14.081 --> 15:15.881
* Like it's all
just temporary *

15:15.914 --> 15:17.549
* Like her toes
are kind of hairy *

15:17.583 --> 15:19.586
* But it's all very well

15:19.619 --> 15:21.620
* 'Cause God knows
I'll never tell *

15:24.323 --> 15:26.725
* When things get rough, he

15:26.759 --> 15:28.394
* Just hides
behind his Buffy *

15:28.427 --> 15:30.062
* Now look
he's getting huffy *

15:30.096 --> 15:32.164
* 'Cause he knows
that I know *

15:32.198 --> 15:35.302
* She clings, she's needy
She's also really greedy *

15:35.335 --> 15:37.269
-* She never--
-* His eyes are beady

15:37.303 --> 15:39.471
* This is my verse, hello
She--*

15:41.508 --> 15:43.710
Look at me!
I'm dancin' crazy!

16:09.001 --> 16:11.971
* You know

16:12.004 --> 16:15.542
* You're quite
the charmer *
* My knight in armor

16:15.575 --> 16:17.710
* You're the cutest
of the Scoobies *

16:17.744 --> 16:20.679
* With your lips
as red as rubies
and your firm yet supple-- *

16:20.712 --> 16:22.315
* Tight embrace

16:35.861 --> 16:37.963
-* He's swell
-* She's sweller

16:37.996 --> 16:39.566
* He'll always
be my feller *

16:39.599 --> 16:43.036
* That's why I'll never
tell her that I'm petrified *

16:43.070 --> 16:45.172
* I've read this tale

16:45.272 --> 16:47.307
* There's wedding
then betrayal *

16:47.340 --> 16:51.077
* I know there'll come the day
I'll want to run and hide *

16:51.110 --> 16:53.245
* I lied

16:53.279 --> 16:56.716
* I said it's easy

16:56.749 --> 17:00.153
* I've tried

17:00.187 --> 17:04.057
* But there's these fears
I can't quell *

17:04.089 --> 17:07.594
* Is she looking
for a pot of gold *

17:07.626 --> 17:11.663
* Will I look good
when I've gotten old *

17:11.698 --> 17:14.433
* Will our life
become too stressful
if I'm never that successful *

17:14.467 --> 17:17.903
* When I get so
worn and wrinkly that I look
like David Brinkley *

17:17.935 --> 17:19.372
-* Am I crazy
-* Am I dreamin'

17:19.405 --> 17:21.540
* Am I marrying
a demon *

17:21.574 --> 17:24.344
* We could
really raise the beam
in makin' marriage a hell *

17:24.376 --> 17:27.247
* So thank God
I'll never tell *

17:27.279 --> 17:29.249
* I swear
that I'll never tell *

17:31.218 --> 17:33.051
* My lips
are sealed *

17:34.787 --> 17:36.888
* I take the Fifth

17:36.923 --> 17:39.259
* Nothing to see
Move it along *

17:40.492 --> 17:42.961
* I'll never
tell *

17:42.994 --> 17:46.432
(laughing)

17:46.465 --> 17:48.201
It's a nightmare,
a plague.
It has to be stopped.

17:48.234 --> 17:50.702
Like a nightmare about a plague.
It was like
we were being watched.

17:50.737 --> 17:53.373
Things just kept pouring out.
Like there was a wall missing
from our apartment.

17:53.405 --> 17:56.308
Like there were only three
walls-- My toes aren't hairy!
My eyes are not beady!

17:56.343 --> 17:59.112
Giles, you gotta stop it.
I am looking into
some leads and I--

17:59.145 --> 18:01.213
Of course!
Clearly our number

18:01.248 --> 18:03.950
is a retro-pastiche
that's never going to be
a breakaway pop hit.

18:03.982 --> 18:05.951
(woman singing)
Work with me,
British man.

18:05.984 --> 18:07.720
Give me an ax and show me
where to point it.

18:07.753 --> 18:09.422
My Xander, it's not quite
that simple,

18:09.455 --> 18:13.058
but I have learned about
some disturbing things...

18:13.092 --> 18:15.961
* I'm asking you
please, no *

18:15.994 --> 18:19.398
* It isn't right
It isn't fair *

18:19.432 --> 18:22.269
* There was
no parking anywhere *

18:22.301 --> 18:25.971
* I think that hydrant
wasn't there *

18:26.005 --> 18:28.607
* Why can't you
let it go *

18:28.641 --> 18:30.676
As in burnt up?

18:30.710 --> 18:33.512
Somebody set
people on fire?
That's nuts.

18:33.546 --> 18:35.847
I don't know.
One more verse
of our little ditty,

18:35.882 --> 18:38.116
