Anya, Tara.

41:45.269 --> 41:49.206
* Don't give me songs

41:49.239 --> 41:53.344
* Give me something
to sing about *

41:53.378 --> 41:59.416
(vocalizing)

41:59.449 --> 42:04.255
* I need something
to sing about *

42:04.289 --> 42:09.027
(vocalizing)

42:15.766 --> 42:21.239
* Life's a song
you don't get to rehearse *

42:21.271 --> 42:24.775
* And every single verse

42:24.809 --> 42:29.347
* Can make it
that much worse *

42:29.380 --> 42:34.452
* Still my friends
don't know why I ignore *

42:34.485 --> 42:38.923
* The million things or more

42:38.956 --> 42:43.393
* I should be dancing for

42:43.427 --> 42:47.431
* All the joy life sends
family and friends *

42:47.465 --> 42:51.369
* All the twists and bends
knowing that it ends *

42:51.402 --> 42:56.742
* Well, that depends
on if they let you go *

42:56.775 --> 43:01.847
* On if they know
enough to know *

43:03.081 --> 43:06.652
* That when you've bowed

43:06.684 --> 43:10.922
* You leave the crowd

43:22.800 --> 43:25.936
* There was no pain

43:25.971 --> 43:28.172
* No fear, no doubt

43:28.206 --> 43:31.076
* 'Til they pulled me out

43:31.108 --> 43:33.543
* Of heaven

43:36.882 --> 43:39.349
* So that's my refrain

43:39.384 --> 43:42.253
* I live in hell

43:42.286 --> 43:44.822
* 'Cause I've been expelled

43:44.856 --> 43:47.291
* From heaven

43:48.393 --> 43:52.030
* I think I was in heaven

43:54.065 --> 43:59.336
* So give me something
to sing about *

44:02.673 --> 44:06.643
* Please give me something

44:28.733 --> 44:31.036
(sizzling)

44:36.206 --> 44:38.342
* Life's not a song

44:39.677 --> 44:42.313
* Life isn't bliss

44:42.347 --> 44:44.750
* Life is just this

44:44.782 --> 44:48.119
* It's living

44:51.588 --> 44:55.525
* You'll get along

44:55.559 --> 45:00.264
* The pain that you feel
you only can heal *

45:00.297 --> 45:04.835
* By living

45:04.869 --> 45:09.239
* You have to go on living

45:09.273 --> 45:14.445
* So one of us is living

45:16.246 --> 45:20.717
The hardest thing in this world
is to live in it.

45:25.891 --> 45:27.458
(clapping)

45:28.659 --> 45:30.695
Now, that was
a show-stopping number.

45:30.728 --> 45:33.731
Not quite the fireworks
that I was looking for--

45:33.764 --> 45:37.434
-Get out of here.
-Hmm, I smell power.

45:37.467 --> 45:42.072
I guess the little missus and I
should be on our way.

45:42.106 --> 45:43.373
That's never gonna happen.

45:43.407 --> 45:45.943
(chuckles)
I don't make the rules.

45:45.976 --> 45:48.079
She summoned me.

45:48.112 --> 45:51.382
I so did not.
He keeps saying that.

45:51.416 --> 45:53.650
You have my talisman on,
sweet thing.

45:53.684 --> 45:57.487
Oh, but, no.
I-- I, um--

45:57.521 --> 46:00.625
This-- At the Magic Box,
on the floor-- I was--

46:00.657 --> 46:02.960
I was cleaning,
and I forgot--

46:02.994 --> 46:04.929
But I didn't
summon anything.

46:04.963 --> 46:06.998
Well, now, that's a twist.

46:07.032 --> 46:08.934
If it was in the shop,

46:10.335 --> 46:12.637
then one of us probably--

46:18.309 --> 46:20.911
-Xander!
-Well, I didn't know
what was gonna happen.

46:20.945 --> 46:23.949
I just thought
there were gonna be
dances and songs.

46:23.981 --> 46:27.318
I just wanted to make sure
we'd-we'd work out.

46:27.351 --> 46:29.753
Get a happy ending.

46:29.786 --> 46:32.990
(chuckles)
I think everything
worked out just fine.

46:35.793 --> 46:37.661
Does this mean
that I have to...

46:39.965 --> 46:41.766
be your queen?

46:41.798 --> 46:44.135
It's tempting,

46:44.168 --> 46:47.672
but I think we'll
waive that clause
just this once.

46:47.704 --> 46:51.041
Big smiles, everyone.

46:51.076 --> 46:53.878
You beat the bad guy.

46:53.911 --> 46:56.146
* What a lot of fun

46:56.181 --> 47:00.650
* You guys have been
real swell *

47:02.887 --> 47:05.222
* And there's not a one

47:05.255 --> 47:11.195
* Who can say
this ended well *

47:11.228 --> 47:15.233
* All those secrets
you've been concealing *

47:15.266 --> 47:19.670
* Say you're happy now
